  <CaptionedBlock heading="We Price the Match, Not the Sale" imagePosition="none" variant="dark">
    <p>A note from us, Nelson and Kim. The most expensive mistake in puppy buying is not overpaying by a few hundred dollars; it is bringing home a breed that does not fit your routine. We have talked customers out of the breed they walked in for, and one of those couples left us a five-star review for exactly that steer.</p>
    <p>So before we ever talk numbers, we ask what your day looks like from 8am to 6pm. We'd rather talk you out of the wrong breed than sell you the wrong dog.</p>
    <p>That is the whole pricing philosophy: publish the range, include what a new owner actually needs, and let the match decide the rest. Read more about <a href="/about-us/" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">how we run the shop</a>.</p>
    <div slot="side" class="clay h-full bg-white/10 p-6 sm:p-8">
